    "summary": "A legal professional with experience in handling corporate commercial disputes (including recovery, Insolvency/ bankruptcy matters, cheque bouncing cases etc.) across the sectors practicing at the Delhi High Court, various district courts and tribunals in India.\n\nHe has successfully represented clients from multinationals companies to Government organisations and believes that proper reasoning coupled with strategic planning and timely execution is the key to winning any legal battle. His previous exposure at organisations like United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees, National Green Tribunal, Competition Appellate Tribunal, Coca-Cola India and Ministry of Commerce & Industry, Government of India has contributed to his thought process, whereby he focuses on delivering quality legal service keeping in mind the business decisions of any company. Further, he is actively engaged in providing legal opinions, advisory and consulting on varied legal propositions. \n\nAdvocate Anuraag Mehta completed his school education from Delhi Public School, RK. Puram, New Delhi and thereafter pursued B.B.A. LL.B. (Hon.) from the Northcap University, Gurgaon with specialisation in Corporate Laws. He is currently pursuing Master of Business Laws from National Law School of India University, Bengaluru and LLM in Law & Technology from Tilburg University, The Netherlands. \n\nHe is a dynamic young individual ready to explore opportunities. Creative and enthusiastic, and is always keen to learn new things. Mr. Mehta possess good communication and interpersonal skills. 3C\u2019s - Confident, Cooperative, Consistent.",
