            "description": "Recruited & Managed a team of 16 Individuals, Approached and convinced RWA\u2019s, Schools, Colleges/ Universities, Corporates, Marketplaces to Switch off their non-essential lights to change the climate change. Further, encouraged them to switch to Rooftop solar panels.\n\n\"If we're destroying our trees and destroying our environment and hurting animals and hurting one another and all that stuff, there's got to be a very powerful energy to fight that. I think we need more love in the world. We need more kindness, more compassion, more joy, more laughter. I definitely want to contribute to that\".\n\nEarth hour helps shine a light on climate change. World's largest grass root campaign for environment where world comes together for climate change. Involving people and making them critical actor of it. Earth hour is not only about increasing awareness on to change the climate change but to unite people to protect the planet. A movement initiated by WWF for annually encouraging individuals , communities , households, and businesses to turn off their non-essential lights for a hour. It started from Sydney , Australia in 2007 to engaging mainstream community on broad range of environmental issues."
